  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sustainable Livelihoods through Cooperatives, Renewable Energy and Gender Empowerment in Burundi-MU</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The  overall objective of the  project   is to empower  women farmers and economic actors   financially, economically,  and socially using the  renewable energy.   for this  part of outcome,   the project will ensure the   increase  of  knowledge   of  women  on health, sexual production  and   nutrition  and access on   health facilities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project   has three main outcomes ,   empowering  women coffee farmers   for better link  to remunerative market through strengthened   cooperatives  and  increase Horamama brand, empowering  small-scale  women  palm oil  processors  through  the  use of flexi Biogas system, and  empowering  Marginalised   women and girls socially , economically  through creation of  Sunflower   cooperative  and  better access  to finance .    Mothers&apos; Union will   implement   one part of the 3rd   outcome  with following activities : Sensitize marginalized women and girls on Reproductive Health, Family Planning and Nutrition</narrative>
  </description>
